                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p> Probably from <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1401">15th century</origDate>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The inclusion of the feast for the relics of Uppsala cathedral, <locus from="108ra" to="108va" scheme="folios"/>, suggest that the breviary was intended for the diocese of <placeName ref="Uppsala">Uppsala</placeName>. A former librarian has suggested a church in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100288">Sigtuna</placeName>, see <locus from="Note_1r" to="Note_1r" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Bought together with a similar manuscript, A 102, at the Kyckerström auction in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100089">Uppsala</placeName> 28 March <date when="1855"/>, according to notes in the library archives, see <locus from="Note_1r" to="Note_1r" scheme="other"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
                    <msPart>
                        <msIdentifier>
                            <idno type="codicologicalUnit">1</idno>
                        </msIdentifier>
                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locusGrp>
                                    <locus from="1ra" to="1vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="3ra" to="14vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                </locusGrp>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of time (fragmented)</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">Castissimum marie virginis vterum</incipit>
                                <explicit>quia hic est vere propheta qui venturus est in mundum psalmus Magnificat et cetera</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Almost the whole Proper of time is missing on account of lost quires and pages.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1ra" to="1vb" scheme="folios"/> contains readings, probably for the First and Second Saturday after Epiphany. They are excerpts from sermons by Ps. Augustine and Ps. Maximus.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3ra" to="3vb" scheme="folios"/> contain readings for the feast De prophetis (the beginning is missing); <locus from="3vb" to="5vb" scheme="folios"/> contain readings from Ezek. 2-7 for Sundays and weekdays; <locus from="5vb" to="14va" scheme="folios"/> contain readings and collects for the twenty-five Sundays after Trinity. Despite the inserted dummy-leaves no text is missing between <locus from="3" to="3" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="4" to="4" scheme="folios"/> nor between <locus from="13" to="13" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="14" to="14" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p>On <locus from="14vb" to="14vb" scheme="folios"/> two texts have been added in different contemporary hands. The first contain instructions on how to procede if there are more than twenty-five sundays after Trinity, the second on how to celebrate the Octave for St Andrew.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locusGrp>
                                    <locus from="15ra" to="24vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="2ra" to="2vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="25ra" to="148vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                </locusGrp>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of saints (fragmented)</title>
                                <rubric>In vigilia beati andree apostoli si dominica fuerit legatur omelia dominicalis alioquin de vigiliis Secundum Iohannem</rubric>
                                <incipit>In illo Stabat Iohannes et ex discipulis eius duo (John 1:35)</incipit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The Proper of saints begins with the Vigil for St Andrew and ends with St Linus.</p>
                                    <p> The bottom part of <locus from="148vb" to="148vb" scheme="folios"/> is damaged making it impossible to ascertain that the text for St Linus is complete.</p>
                                    <p> An unknown number of leaves are missing after <locus from="24v" to="24v" scheme="folios"/>, which contains the readings for the third nocturn for St Anne (9 Dec.). The Proper continues on <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>, which should precede <locus from="25r" to="25r" scheme="folios"/>, with the end of the feast of the Purification (2 Feb.). All feasts between 9 Dec. and 2 Febr. are thus missing.</p>
                                    <p> No loss of text between <locus from="30" to="30" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="31" to="31" scheme="folios"/> despite inserted dummy-pages.</p>
                                    <p> On <locus from="40va" to="40va" scheme="folios"/> the Proper of saints ends after what seems to be the fourth reading for St Ambrose (4 April). It is followed by the Common for one martyr in two versions depending on the degree of solemnity. The proper continues on <locus from="41rb" to="41rb" scheme="folios"/> with Sts Tiburtius and Valerianus (14 Apr.). Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="23ra" to="24vb" scheme="folios"/>: St Anne (9 Dec.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="70va" to="71rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Botvid (28 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="108rb" to="108va" scheme="folios"/>: Feast for the relics;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="116vb" to="120ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Birgitta (7 Oct.).</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="149ra" to="150ra" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Office of the Virgin Mary</title>
                                <rubric>In commemoracione beate marie virginis ad uesperas super psalmos feriales antiphona</rubric>
                                <incipit>STella maria maris paris expers nos tuearis</incipit>
                                <explicit>sis post luctus terminum mitis consolatrix collecta Concede nos et cetera</explicit>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/101547">AH 5</title>
                                    <citedRange from="21" to="21" unit="number"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="150ra" to="150va" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Suffrages</title>
                                <rubric>Hic notatur suffragia que habenda sunt in sabbatis de patronis primo in vesperis de sancto laurencio per antiphona</rubric>
                                <incipit>Que martir gloriose</incipit>
                                <explicit>versus Ora pro nobis collecta omnipotens sempiterne de reliquis sicut in vesperis</explicit>
                                <note>Two sets of suffrages each, for Saturdays and Christmas, for St Lawrence, St Erik, St Henrik and the relics.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="150va" to="159rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Readings</title>
                                <rubric>De beata virgine in sabbatis legenda Sermo beati augustini Sabbato primo</rubric>
                                <incipit>Adest nobis dilectissimi dies venerabilis virgini dedicatus </incipit>
                                <explicit>Illic enim agnouit bos possessorem suum et asinus presepe domini sui (Isa 1:3) Tu autem domine</explicit>
                                <note>This sections contains sermons by Augustine, Jerome, Bernhard of Clairvaux, Maximus and Fulbert of Chartres. There are quite a few agreements with the readings in Breviarium Upsalense (printed) 1496 as regards the texts on <locus from="150v" to="154v" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="159rb" to="172v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Common of saints (fragmented)</title>
                                <rubric>IN vigila vnius apostoli ad ix capitulum</rubric>
                                <incipit>
                                    <sic>DDominus</sic> sapiencia fundauit terram (Prov. 3:19) </incipit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> No text is missing between <locus from="159" to="159" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="160" to="160" scheme="folios"/> despite the change of hands and the inserted dummy pages.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="159rb" to="161vb" scheme="folios"/>: Common for apostles;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="161vb" to="164ra" scheme="folios"/>: Common for evangelists;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="164ra" to="165va" scheme="folios"/>: Common for one martyr (no text is missing despite the dummy pages inserted between <locus from="164" to="164" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="165" to="165" scheme="folios"/>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="165va" to="167rb" scheme="folios"/>: Common for many martyrs (no text is missing despite the dummy page inserted between <locus from="165" to="165" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="166" to="166" scheme="folios"/>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="167Arb" to="168vb" scheme="folios"/>: Common for a confessor and bishop (the text runs uninterrupted from <locus from="167Av" to="167Av" scheme="folios"/>, to the inserted note <locus from="167B" to="167B" scheme="folios"/> and on to <locus from="168r" to="168r" scheme="folios"/>, despite the change of hands);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="168vb" to="169va" scheme="folios"/>: Common for a confessor not bishop;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="169va" to="171va" scheme="folios"/>: Common for many confessors (the leaves have become disordered in the conservation process. Correct order: <locus from="169" to="169" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="171" to="171" scheme="folios"/>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="171va" to="172vb" scheme="folios"/>: Common for a virgin (the leaves have become disordered in the conservation process. Correct order: <locus from="171" to="171" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="170" to="170" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="172" to="172" scheme="folios"/>, despite the change of hands);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="172va" to="172vb" scheme="folios"/>: Common for many virgins, ends imperfectly.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="173r" to="173v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Office for the Maccabees</title>
                                <rubric>hic ordinaliter habentur<unclear quantity="2" unit="chars" reason="illegible"/>
                                </rubric>
                                <incipit>Reconcilietur vobis nec vos deferat (2 Macc. 1:5)</incipit>
                                <explicit>versus Et nunc clamemus in ce<supplied reason="omitted">lum</supplied> et mise<supplied reason="omitted">rebitur</supplied> nos Dominus noster</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="174r" to="174v" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="175ra" to="177vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Readings (fragmented)</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">Spiritus quoque leuauit me (Ezek. 3:14)</incipit>
                                <explicit>pestia et fames intrinsecus (Ezek. 7:15) Tu autem domine</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Expliciunt legende de tempore per estatem In dominicis et feriis</finalRubric>
                                <note>The beginning of the readings seems to be missing.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="177vb" to="185vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Homilies (fragmented)</title>
                                <rubric>Incipiunt Omelia dominicales et primo Dominica prima post trinitatis Secundum Lucam</rubric>
                                <incipit>IN illo tempore dixit ihesus discipulis homo quidam erat diues (Luke 16:19)</incipit>
                                <explicit>surdus erraret et mutus Exiens ihesus de finibus <gap reason="editorial"/> fines decapoleos (Mark 7:13) alleluia <supplied reason="omitted">V</supplied>erbum omnia</explicit>
                                <note>The end of this part is missing. The last text is Bede's homily for the Twelfth Sunday after Trinity on Mark 7:31.</note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
