                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="186" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>The binding, whole quires and single leaves are missing. Some leaves must have been missing already in the fifteenth century, since leaves with the missing text have been supplied, see e.g. <locus from="160r" to="167Br" scheme="folios"/>. The extant quires are loose and the condition of the quires and leaves is poor. The paper is brittle and shows signs of corrosion from the ink. Parts are missing from some leaves, e.g. <locus from="1" to="2" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="149" to="149" scheme="folios"/>. A preservation of the leaves was made in 1974, which is probably when some pages were reinforced and a number of dummy-pages added for support. Some leaves have become unordered in the conservation process and dummy-pages have sometimes been inserted where no leaves are missing, giving the impression that text has been lost, see description in Contents.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
